1	//! Graph GENERATION (BEHAVIOR.md §6): mapping a proof-state / constraint-system
2	//! description onto the DOT [`Graph`] model, over an independent input model
3	//! designed from observed paired `main/proof` sequents and `interactive-graph-def`
4	//! graphs.
5	//!
6	//! What the observed system→graph mapping does, structurally (each point traces to
7	//! corpus/live observation — see BEHAVIOR.md §6):
8	//!   * a **rule instance** `#t : Rule[actions]` becomes a `record` node with up to
9	//!     three groups `{premises}|{info}|{conclusions}`; the **info** group (the
10	//!     `#t : Rule[…]` cell) is always present (100 % of 160 409 corpus records),
11	//!     and an **empty** premise or conclusion group is dropped (so a source rule
12	//!     with no premises renders `{info}|{concl}`);
13	//!   * an intruder-knowledge fact renders as a gray `!KU( m ) @ #t` **ellipse**;
14	//!     a protocol action/event as a darkblue `Fact @ #t` ellipse; a compressed
15	//!     intruder rule as an uncolored `#t : rule` ellipse;
16	//!   * an unresolved node referenced by an open premise renders as an
17	//!     **invtrapezium** `(#var, idx)` (BEHAVIOR.md §3d);
18	//!   * **edges** connect a conclusion port to a premise port (structural), or an
19	//!     intruder deduction (red dashed), message (gray30), temporal order (blue3 /
20	//!     black dashed), etc. — the finite observed style vocabulary (§3c);
21	//!   * `n<K>` ids come from [`crate::alloc`]; the header is inferred by role (§4).
22	//!
23	//! GAPS (need the GPL solver; not derivable from output): *which* nodes/edges a
24	//! raw constraint system yields (the compression content), the per-rule color
25	//! hash, and record-cell line wrapping. This layer takes node/edge lists, colors,
26	//! and pre-rendered cell text as INPUTS and assembles the exact DOT structure.
27	
28	use crate::alloc::NodeIdAllocator;
29	use crate::model::*;
30	use crate::render::{escape_record, Fact};
31	
32	/// A rule instance: one record node with premise / info / conclusion cells.
33	#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
34	pub struct RuleInstance {
35	    pub temporal: String,
36	    pub rule: String,
37	    pub role: String,
38	    pub premises: Vec<Fact>,
39	    pub actions: Vec<Fact>,
40	    pub conclusions: Vec<Fact>,
41	    /// Per-rule fill color (a solver-side hash — a GAP; supplied by the caller).
42	    pub fillcolor: String,
43	    /// `black` on the light MSR palette, `white` on the saturated role palette.
44	    pub fontcolor: String,
45	}
